Lipová is a village situated in the Prostějov District, Olomouc Region, Czech Republic.
The village consists of three areas: Lipová, Hrochov and Seč. On 13 November 2006 it had a population of 767, consisting of 98 children under 15, 330 women and 339 men.


== History ==
The earliest known record of the village is from 1379.


